article_title: Without Obamacare, Jobs Report Might've Been Worse

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: The Affordable Care Act, which is infusing millions of new paying customers into the economy who previously couldn’t afford medical care services, continues to boost jobs growth as the health industry emphasizes outpatient care and value-based medicine.
